SIMPLE: martlet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Martlet
<hw>Mart"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>martinet</ets>. See <er>Martin</er> the bird, and cf.
<er>Martinet</er> a disciplinarian.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European house
martin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>merlette</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A bird without beak or feet; -- generally assumed
to represent a <sig>martin</sig>. As a mark of cadency it denotes the
fourth son.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martyniaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
